Saying the gift would immeasurably improve their understanding of the ineffable quality that makes certain big-screen stars positively radiate, researchers at the University of California Los Angeles announced Tuesday that A-list actor Leonardo DiCaprio has agreed to donate his it-factor to science.Sources said the 40-year-old actor, known for his roles in such critically and commercially successful films as and , granted the team of experts at UCLA permission to remove and preserve his for study upon his death.